er combining the transaction summary into a grouped accessibility element or providing a synthesized accessibility label/value that reads as a single summary, while hiding decorative sub-elements from accessibility where appropriate.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"STATUS_INFORMATION_APPEARS_IN_MULTIPLE_PLACES\",\n      \"category\": \"verbosity\",\n      \"severity\": \"low\",\n      \"confidence\": \"medium\",\n      \"rationale\": \"Card status is represented both by a header status dot and by the visible \\\"Locked\\\" or \\\"Active\\\" text in the card details section. Even if the dot is later hidden from accessibility, the layout suggests repeated status cues within a compact card.\",\n      \"potential_user_impact\": \"If both are exposed, spoken output may feel repetitive and distract from the more important financial details and actions in a time-sensitive fraud review flow.\",\n      \"suggested_improvement\": \"Ensure only one clear spoken representation of card status is exposed in the accessibility tree, preferably the textual status near the card details.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"BUTTON_LABELS_LACK_TRANSACTION_CONTEXT\",\n      \"category\": \"label_clarity\",\n      \"severity\": \"medium\",\n      \"confidence\": \"high\",\n      \"rationale\": \"The footer actions use short labels, especially \\\"Report issue\\\" and \\\"This was me.\\\" In isolation, these are understandable visually within the card, but when announced out of context they may not fully convey that they apply to the flagged transaction review.\",\n      \"potential_user_impact\": \"Screen reader users navigating by buttons may hear labels that are terse and context-dependent, making it harder to distinguish these actions from other buttons elsewhere in a financial app.\",\n      \"suggested_improvement\": \"Provide more contextual accessibility labels such as \\\"Report issue with this transaction\\\" and \\\"This transaction was mine\\\" while preserving the concise visible text.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"FINANCIAL_DECISION_FLOW_COULD_INCREASE_COGNITIVE_LOAD\",\n      \"category\": \"cognitive_load\",\n      \"severity\": \"medium\",\n      \"confidence\": \"medium\",\n      \"rationale\": \"The card combines review, dispute categorization, card locking, merchant notification, confirmation, and support call actions in one container. This is efficient visually, but for assistive technology users it creates a dense sequence of unrelated decisions inside a single reading path.\",\n      \"potential_user_impact\": \"Users may experience higher cognitive load when trying to understand which controls are optional, which are immediate state changes, and which finalize the fraud response. In a stressful security scenario, this can impair confidence and accuracy.\",\n      \"suggested_improvement\": \"Improve hierarchy for accessibility by grouping sections semantically and adding concise section-level labels or summaries so users can better distinguish transaction details, review choices, card controls, and final actions.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"CALL_ACTION_LABEL_MAY_BE_TOO_GENERIC\",\n      \"category\": \"label_clarity\",\n      \"severity\": \"low\",\n      \"confidence\": \"high\",\n      \"rationale\": \"The help action is labeled only \\\"Call\\\" next to \\\"Need help?\\\" Visually this is clear enough, but the actionable label itself is generic when encountered through screen reader navigation.\",\n      \"potential_user_impact\": \"A VoiceOver user navigating by controls may not know who will be called or why, reducing confidence before activating a support-related action in a fraud context.\",\n      \"suggested_improvement\": \"Use a more descriptive accessibility label such as \\\"Call support\\\" or \\\"Call fraud support\\\" while keeping the visible pill text brief.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"runtime_validation_recommended\": [\n    {\n      \"area\": \"spoken_output\",\n      \"reason\": \"Runtime testing is needed to confirm whether the transaction summary and status are announced as fragmented, repetitive, or context-poor in VoiceOver.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"area\": \"focus_order\",\n      \"reason\": \"The card contains several distinct decision areas; runtime validation should confirm whether swipe navigation preserves a logical review-to-action sequence.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"area\": \"dynamic_type\",\n      \"reason\": \"This component packs long reason labels, dual footer buttons, and multiple explanatory texts into a dense card; larger text sizes may increase wrapping and cognitive load.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"analysis_confidence\": \"medium\"\n}"
